<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 02 at 3:29AM EDT  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Mason,
northeastern Putnam, northwestern Roane and southern Jackson Counties
through 400 AM EDT...
At 329 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Kenna, or 7 miles southwest of Ripley, moving east
at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Ripley, Spencer, Kenna, Reedy, Statts Mills, Evans, Harmony, Given,
Kentuck, Fairplain, Gay and Gandeeville.
This includes Interstate 77 in West Virginia between mile markers 123
and 139.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
